    b"te the current conversation and produce memory search hints for\x0d\x0a        the sel"
    b"ected task.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before the selected ta"
    b"sk runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once the hints look good enough for the request without"
    b" thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact "
    b"memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: case-"
    b"insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring agai"
    b"nst searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Eac"
    b"h value is checked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchable memory conte"
    b"nt.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_mem"
    b"ory: a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve."
    b"\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidate_me"
    b"mory.\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be"
    b" useful\x0d\x0a          when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - Pref"
    b"er tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless"
    b" compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only fo"
    b"r clear exclusions.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable words or phrases"
    b" that should appear\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings."
    b"equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0d\x0a          memory value "
    b"as a whole.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints over broad keywor"
    b"d stuffing.\x0d\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful search hint is availab"
    b"le.\x0d\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        {{ _.r"
    b"ole(\"user\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Current user request:\x0d\x0a        {{ current_user_request"
    b" }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Conversation history for the current session:\x0d\x0a        {% for con"
    b"versation in session_conversations %}\x0d\x0a        Conversation:\x0d\x0a          id: {{ c"
    b"onversation.id }}\x0d\x0a          name: {{ conversation.name }}\x0d\x0a          created_at"
